## Current Project State (snapshot)

Alpha desktop UI available. Multi-crate Cargo workspace under `crates/`. SQLite + FTS5 storage,
sqlite-vec ANN search, catalog-driven provider selection, unified inference queue
(`InferenceQueue`), hybrid search pipeline, bulk graph access (`get_all_edges`,
`get_nodes_paginated`). Interactive RAG chat REPL (`cli_chat`). Native GPUI desktop app
with graph canvas, schema-driven node editor, FTS5/semantic/hybrid search panel, and
streaming LLM chat panel with rig-based agent tool loop (collapsible tool calls, streaming reasoning). No active bugs.

UI crates (see `feature_UI.md`):
- `u-forge-graph-view` — `GraphSnapshot` + `build_snapshot()`, force-directed layout (grid-cell bucketed O(N) repulsion), R-tree spatial index, viewport culling, `rebuild_spatial_index()`.
- `u-forge-ui-traits` — `DrawCommand` / `Viewport` / `generate_draw_commands()` rendering pipeline (culling, LOD, type-color). Framework-agnostic. `pub fn node_color_for_type(name: &str) -> [u8; 4]` assigns stable, distinct colors via FNV-1a hash + golden-angle hue scatter — any type name gets a color with no code changes.
- `u-forge-agent` — Rig-based LLM agent crate. Five `rig::tool::Tool` impls: `FtsSearchTool` (FTS5 keyword), `SemanticSearchTool` (ANN embedding via `InferenceQueue`), `HybridSearchTool` (RRF + reranking), `UpsertNodeTool` (create/update nodes with immediate re-chunking + embedding), `UpsertEdgeTool` (create/update edges with endpoint re-embedding). Write tools block until DB + all embeddings (standard + HQ) are stored. `GraphAgent` wraps a `CompletionsClient` pointed at Lemonade's OpenAI-compatible endpoint; holds `hq_queue: Option<Arc<InferenceQueue>>` so write tools can trigger HQ embedding. `prompt_stream()` drives rig's multi-turn tool loop with all five tools and emits `AgentStreamEvent` variants over `mpsc::channel`: `ReasoningDelta`, `TextDelta`, `ToolCallStart`, `ToolResult`, `Done`, `Error`. `fts5_sanitize` logic is inlined (not re-exported from `u-forge-core`). `ToolError` (renamed from `SearchToolError`) is the shared error type for all five tools.
- `u-forge-ui-gpui` — GPUI 0.2.2 canvas app. Modular crate: `main.rs` is the binary entry point only; all types live in a library target. Modules: `selection_model` (shared selection state), `text_field` (`TextFieldView` custom input implementing `EntityInputHandler`; single-line horizontal scroll, multiline vertical scroll), `tree_panel` (resizable sidebar, uses `w_full()`), `search_panel` (`SearchPanel` entity with FTS5/Semantic/Hybrid modes, inline query field, results list), `chat_history` (`ChatHistoryStore` — SQLite-backed session persistence at `<db_path>/chat_history.db`; `chat_sessions` + `chat_messages` tables; `create_session`, `list_sessions`, `load_messages`, `save_session`, `delete_session`), `chat_panel` (`ChatPanel` entity — streaming LLM chat; **header**: chat history session selector dropdown (title button + "New" button; delete ✕ per row; dismisses on click outside); **input area**: multiline text field + Send button + enter-to-submit toggle + model selector dropdown below input; all downloaded LLM models shown (uses `select_all_llm_models()`), defaults to preferred device model from `[chat.gpu/npu/cpu].model`; session auto-saves on stream completion; resumes most-recent session on startup; when `GraphAgent` is set routes through agent tool loop; `ChatRole::ToolCall` entries are collapsible with purple accent; thinking/reasoning shown for both paths), `graph_canvas` (pan/zoom canvas), `node_editor/` (3 files: struct+methods, field specs, render impl), `app_view/` (2 files: data ops + marker types, render impl). See `feature_UI.md` → "Module structure" table for the full breakdown. `AppView` root view: 28 px menu bar + horizontal body (`overflow_hidden()` flex row): optional left sidebar (default 220 px, user-resizable) showing either `TreePanel` or `SearchPanel` based on `SidebarTab` enum + vertical workspace (`NodeEditorPanel` / graph canvas, default 30/70 split, user-resizable) + optional `ChatPanel` (default 280 px, user-resizable). Status bar "Tree" / "Search" buttons toggle sidebar tab; clicking active tab closes sidebar. `AppView` holds `Arc<tokio::runtime::Runtime>`, `Arc<AppConfig>`, `Option<InferenceQueue>` (standard + HQ); `do_init_lemonade()` discovers Lemonade asynchronously on startup, builds a `LemonadeChatProvider` and a `GraphAgent` (passing `hq_queue` so write tools can trigger HQ embedding), pushes both to `ChatPanel`, and triggers bulk embedding. Embedding progress shown in amber in the status bar center. `SelectionModel` entity shared by `TreePanel`, `SearchPanel`, `GraphCanvas`, and `NodeEditorPanel`; `cx.observe()` keeps all in sync — tree/search clicks pan the canvas and open editor tabs. `NodeEditorPanel` provides browser-style tabs (pin/unpin/close), schema-driven form rendering — field kinds (Text, Array, Boolean, Enum, Number) driven by schema type; runtime-type fallback for fields not in the schema. Dirty-state tracking (orange tab indicator), multi-column layout with pagination, save-all (Ctrl+S persists dirty tabs + layout + triggers per-node `rechunk_and_embed` for all saved nodes so semantic search stays current). `GraphCanvas` holds `canvas_bounds: Arc<RwLock<Bounds<Pixels>>>` updated each paint frame; all `window.paint_*` calls add `bounds.origin` offset and `overflow_hidden()` clips output to the pane. **Graph legend and `TreePanel` type-header colors both call `node_color_for_type` — they are always in sync with the canvas node colors.** Run: `cargo run -p u-forge-ui-gpui`. **`TextFieldView` renders text via `shape_line`/`shape_text` + `paint()` on a canvas (NOT as a div `SharedString` child) — cursor uses `x_for_index`/`position_for_index`, clicks use `closest_index_for_x`/`closest_index_for_position` on the cached `TextFieldLayout`. Line height = `font_size * 1.618` (GPUI's `phi()` default). Never place text as div child if pixel-exact cursor overlay is needed.**
- `u-forge-core` — `node_positions` table added to SQLite schema; `KnowledgeGraph::save_layout()` / `load_layout()` persist and restore canvas positions. `build_snapshot()` applies saved positions after force-directed layout, so new nodes get computed positions and known nodes restore their last user-placed position. `SchemaManager::get_object_type_schema()` provides sync cache-based lookup for UI use (async `load_schema` must be called first to populate cache). `rechunk_and_embed(graph, queue, hq_queue, object_id)` is the per-node analogue of `embed_all_chunks` — deletes old chunks, flattens metadata + edges, creates new chunks, embeds all (standard + HQ), and blocks until complete. `delete_chunks_for_node(object_id)` added to `KnowledgeGraph` for chunk replacement. `PropertyType` now re-exported from `lib.rs`. Canonical data format: `defaults/data/memory.jsonl` — `entitytype`/`nodetype`/`properties` with typed JSON values (native arrays, not comma-separated strings). Legacy MemoryMesh format can be converted via `cargo run --example convert_memorymesh`.

Recent quality improvements:
- `load_model()` now accepts `already_loaded: &[String]` — if the model ID is in the slice the HTTP round-trip to `/api/v1/load` is skipped entirely. Callers extract these IDs from `catalog.loaded` (already fetched by `LemonadeServerCatalog::discover`). `ProviderFactory::build` threads this parameter through all capability branches. Both CLI demos extract the loaded-model list from the catalog and fire all provider builds concurrently via `futures::future::join_all` / `tokio::join!`, eliminating sequential load waits on warm servers.
- `embed_all_chunks` is now incremental — uses `get_unembedded_chunks` / `get_unembedded_chunks_hq` (LEFT JOIN on `chunks_vec`) instead of re-scanning all objects.
- Hybrid search diagnostic blocks demoted from `info!` to `debug!` — no more log spam in production; `RUST_LOG=u_forge_core::search=debug` reveals full pipeline state.
- `KnowledgeGraphStorage` now uses `parking_lot::Mutex` — all 24 `.lock().unwrap()` calls removed.
- `ObjectType` enum deleted from `types.rs` — it was dead code; `ObjectMetadata.object_type` is `String` throughout, and `ObjectBuilder` already embeds correct string literals.
- `WeightedEmbedDispatcher::worker_count()` removed — `InferenceQueue` exposes `embedding_worker_count()` for callers. `WeightedWorkerSlot::name` and `idle` fields annotated with intent comments (retained for future diagnostics).
- HTTP timeouts added to all Lemonade HTTP clients — `LemonadeHttpClient::new()` sets 30s request / 5s connect; lightweight discovery clients (`system_info`, `catalog`) use 5s / 2s. Prevents indefinite blocking when Lemonade Server hangs.
- Token estimation changed from `len / 4` to `len.div_ceil(3)` — conservative 3-char/token ratio better matches dense TTRPG prose. `split_text()` in `text.rs` uses the same ratio (`MAX_CHUNK_TOKENS * 3` chars per chunk).
- `EdgeType` collapsed from single-variant enum (`Custom(String)`) to transparent newtype struct. Use `EdgeType::new(s)` everywhere — `Custom(s)` no longer exists.
- `ObjectId` and `ChunkId` promoted from type aliases to newtype structs (`#[serde(transparent)]`). The compiler now rejects passing a `ChunkId` where an `ObjectId` is expected. Construct with `::new_v4()`; parse with `::parse_str(s)`.
- 9 clippy warnings resolved: `while let` loop, boxed large enum variant (`ProviderSlot::Tts`), `#[derive(Default)]` on `KokoroVoice`, transmute type annotation for sqlite-vec FFI, doc formatting. Edge metadata JSON parse failures now emit `debug!()` instead of silently swallowing errors.
- BPE tokenizer cached via `LazyLock<CoreBPE>` in `text.rs` and `u-forge-agent/lib.rs` — `tiktoken_rs::o200k_harmony()` was constructing a ~200k-entry vocabulary on every `count_tokens()` call, causing `split_text()` to hang on long inputs. `TextChunk::new` also uses the cached tokenizer.

The core library has been fully refactored (hardware abstraction layer removed):
- `hardware/` directory deleted — `NpuDevice`, `GpuDevice`, `CpuDevice`, `DeviceWorker`
  trait, and `HardwareBackend` enum no longer exist.
- `lemonade/device_factory.rs`, `lemonade/model_limits.rs`, `lemonade/registry.rs`,
  `lemonade/stack.rs` deleted. `LemonadeModelRegistry`, `ModelRole`, `LemonadeStack`,
  `EmbeddingManager`, and `TranscriptionManager` no longer exist.
- Replaced by: `lemonade/catalog.rs` (`LemonadeServerCatalog`), `lemonade/selector.rs`
  (`ModelSelector`, `SelectedModel`, `QualityTier`), `lemonade/duplicate_guard.rs`
  (`DuplicateGuard`), `lemonade/provider_factory.rs` (`ProviderFactory`, `Capability`,
  `BuiltProvider`).
- `ai/embeddings.rs` and `ai/transcription.rs` are trait-only files; implementations
  live in `lemonade/embedding.rs` and `lemonade/transcription.rs`.
- `InferenceQueueBuilder` now wires providers via `.with_provider(BuiltProvider)` /
  `.with_providers(Vec<BuiltProvider>)`. `ProviderFactory::build()` constructs them.
- `AppConfig` includes `[chat]` with per-device model overrides (`[chat.gpu]`, `[chat.npu]`) and `[storage]` with `db_path` (default `./data/db`). `ModelConfig.load_params` replaces the old `context_limits: HashMap`.

